The gallery was then cleared, and the house divided,
when there appeared for the second reading,–Ayes, 52;
Noes, 40 : majority in favour of the second reading, 12.

Abstract of American Finances, as laid before
Congress, January 23, by Alexander Hamilton, Esq;
Secretary to the Treasury of the United States.

 "I hire a small room for 12 dollars a month, and sleep on 
the ground;
                    borrowed a chair, and bought some crockery. 
No such thing as a tavern;
                    never was. Letters of no use; 
no one asks me to his house. I go to bed at
                    eight o'clock 
to kill time. A play twice a week; the most fashionable

ladies stand up in the front boxes, and light a segar by the

chandelier; the house filled with smoke.
